ruby_text = 'A ruby is a pink to blood-red colored gemstone , a variety of the mineral  corundum ( aluminium oxide ). The red color is caused mainly by the presence of the element chromium . Its name comes from ruber , Latin for red. Other varieties of gem-quality corundum are called sapphires . The ruby is considered one of the four precious stones , together with the sapphire , the emerald , and the diamond . [ 1 ]'

